        <mxCell id="qDj99eJ1U_vqVaamxmj_-409" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;snapToPoint=0;fixDash=0;" value="files" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="60" x="2043" y="788.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="qDj99eJ1U_vqVaamxmj_-360" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontStyle=0;fontSize=13;align=left;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;fontColor=#333333;fontFamily=Helvetica;snapToPoint=0;fixDash=0;" value="&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Workflow&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;1.)&lt;/b&gt; Initialize DB from RAW Data btn press&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;2.) &lt;/b&gt;DNS&amp;nbsp;A Record forwards to Hetzner LB&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;3.)&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Client Machine (Frontend) sends HTTP request to Backend REST API&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(51, 51, 51), rgb(193, 193, 193)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;4.) &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(51, 51, 51), rgb(193, 193, 193)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Backend Rest API validates user&#39;s admin access and invokes API Gateway&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(51, 51, 51), rgb(193, 193, 193));&quot;&gt;5.) &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(51, 51, 51), rgb(193, 193, 193));&quot;&gt;API GW invokes Raw Data ETL Lambda&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;6.) &lt;/b&gt;Lambda has sheet URL as environment variable, downloads sheet to memory -&amp;gt; Transforms Raw Data to individual sheets -&amp;gt; Creates TSV file for each sheet&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;7.) &lt;/b&gt;Lambda uploads original sheet as backup &amp;amp; processed TSV files to S3 Bucket&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;8.) &lt;/b&gt;Lambda generates pre-signed s3 object urls&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;9.) &lt;/b&gt;API GW receives response from Lambda with TSV file urls, returning them to Backend&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;10.)&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Backend takes response from API GW with TSV file urls &amp;amp; downloads TSV files from S3 bucket into server storage&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;11.) &lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Backend extracts raw TSV strings from storage TSV files, passing each payload to individual Backend REST API TSV endpoints directly via localhost BASE_URL&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;12.) &lt;/b&gt;Backend REST API transforms RAW TSV strings into SQL DML &amp;amp; responds to Frontend step 3 with all PSQL statements, then clears memory&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;13.) &lt;/b&gt;Frontend displays PSQL statements in unique tabs per TSV file for verification&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;14.)&lt;/b&gt; Verify the generated DML Statements &amp;amp;query the postgres database /w INSERTS&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="507" width="280" x="890" y="783" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
